y and popular imagination.Valentinian Christianity: Texts and Translations brings together for the first time all the extant texts composed by Valentinus and his followers. With fresh, carefully annotated translations throughout and new transcriptions of the original Greek, Latin, and Coptic on facing pages, Geoffrey S. Smith provides an illuminating, balanced overview of Valentinian Christianity and its formative place in Christian history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aChurch historyyPrimitive and early church, ca. 30-600vSources. 0aGnostic literature. 0aValentiniansxHistoryvSources. 7aRELIGION / Ancient.2bisacsh  aaccessible.  aegyptian christian.  aformative place in christian history.  alarge and influential sect of christianity.  aoriginal greek and coptic manuscripts.  aoverview of valentinian christianity.  aresurrected gnostic gospels.  asecond and third centuries.  ateach brand of theology.  atraveled to rome.  avalentinians.  avalentinus.1 aSmith, Geoffrey S.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishz978311070477808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020z9783110704570oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520969803zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520969803423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520969803.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020